nodes.message: Hi there, are you getting this?
Quick check first! What is your name?
What do you remember of some old chats?
That is great! We have the UI up and working!
Hi Bob, back to test a bit more, had to drop out of the earlier chat sorry
Well one test was the format of your response which I am happy to say looks good!
Well I need to test the end chat button. Will try that shortly
bye
Hi there, I'm back. I've backed up everything to git and the exit button is working good. It triggers the bye command on pressing it fine

I have dozens of things I want to add. I want to incorporate some buttons to create new personalities either from scratch or from an epub. Then I want to be able to create personalities from a text file of messages or tweets. SOmething like that. You ever read The Prefect by Alastair Reynolds? It has the concept of Beta versions of people and I want to make a basic version of that
I already got the personality creation from epubs built. I just need to add buttons for it. Good point on default personality templates and your beta version feedback
bye
Hi there can I run the usual test. What is your name?
No! It is not! Check your memory!
What went wrong?
Its okay we got there in the end
Before we chat how do you think I could prevent that issue in the future where you forget your name?
It is stored persistently in your primary personality file. I think I will add a point there though in the key "Dos" section
Will do thanks! Now are you aware of Neuromancer? It was written in the 80's right?

I am about halfway through. It is interesting so far and frankly impressive that it was written 40 years ago. It isn't the best book I've read in that it can be a little hard to follow at times but it is good

The concepts for the future such as of AI and technology seem very good for the age of the book. The author captures well what feels like the internet in this cyberpunk setting. It doesn't read as old as it is. The AI's feel perfectly possible based on our current trajectory really

Chase is the one that easiest to understand due to the books focus on him, also Dixie is interested as what I think is a virtual download of a person, is that right? Chase dependence on technology and craving early on when he lost access to the cyberverse reminds me of people craving connection to social media
bye
Hi Bob, how's things?
bye

Performance, errors, anything that comes up really. Later I want to have a visual graph of your memories and which ones got pulled too
Good ideas, will come back later to chat through how they went
bye

Just making dinner

good idea! will do. Back later
